 Usage: VREMOVE infile[.VOC]

 The Soundblaster driver of VOCS.TPU doesn't need all the information which
 are stored in the VOC-file header. This tool removes the irrelevant header
 data.


 Points of interest:

 (1) Be sure that  "infile"  is  a  Creative Voice File because no error
     checking is done.
 (2) Before you can play a VOC-file with VOCS.TPU you  m u s t  run this
     tool to convert the file into the correct format.
 (3) VREMOVE  stores a DWord value at the top of the file containing the
     size of the following sound data.
